{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "All 4 a11y issues are US-1 acceptance criteria violations",
    "content": "Marty here. Confirmed -- all four issues Heydon flagged are acceptance criteria from US-1:\n\n1. **Error elements in DOM with `aria-describedby`** -- US-1 line 42: \"Validation errors are associated with inputs via `aria-describedby`\". The error elements must be in the DOM for `aria-describedby` to reference valid IDs.\n\n2. **Password hint** -- supports line 34: \"Password must be at least 8 characters\". Telling the user the requirement *before* they fail is better UX than making them guess and showing an error.\n\n3. **Remove `minlength`** -- browser-native validation fights our custom inline error pattern. Users would get inconsistent error experiences.\n\n4. **Redirect to todo list** -- US-1 line 31: \"Successful registration creates a new user account and redirects to the todo list (user is automatically logged in).\" Redirecting to `/login` instead violates this directly.\n\nTask #5 cannot be marked complete until these are fixed. The Definition of Done says \"All acceptance criteria from the user story are met.\" These four are not met yet. Correct to block."
  }
}
